Algorithm: DevSecOps Secure CI/CD Pipeline
Start the pipeline.
Monitor the Git repository for code changes.
Trigger the pipeline when code is pushed to the main or develop branch.
Checkout the latest source code from the repository.
Install all required dependencies and tools.
Perform Static Code Analysis to identify coding issues and security vulnerabilities.
Run Dependency Scan to detect vulnerable third-party libraries.
Execute Unit Tests to verify that the application functions correctly.
Build the application if all previous stages are successful.
Scan the Build Artifact/Container Image for security vulnerabilities.
Deploy the application to the testing or staging environment.
Run Security Validation to ensure the deployed application is secure.
If all checks pass, deploy the application to the production environment.
Generate logs and reports for build, testing, and security scan results.
End the pipeline.